gomodel:SYNGO_984  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Myosin Va shows a partial colocalization with GluR1 and GluR2 subunits in primary neuronal cultures (Fig. 2a,b).. Experimental description: Organotypic cultures of hippocampal slices were prepared from postnatal day 5-6 rats.\n\n28/6/2017 Pim\n- Myo5A overexpression construct was of *mouse* origin: \"The C-terminal sequences (globular tails) of mouse myosin Va (amino acids 1,473-1,880), rat myosin Vb (amino acids 1,436 to 1,846) and human myosin VI (amino acids 835 to 1,285) were cloned upstream of the coding sequence of enhanced GFP (Clontech)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_984" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

